 Four out of the six gubernatorial aspirants have withdrawn from today’s primary election of the Lagos State chapter of the People’s Democratic Party (PDP). The chairman of the electoral committee, Emmanuel Ogidi, announced that Deji Doherty, Ade Dosunmu, Rhodes Gbadebo and Jimi Kamal have submitted their withdrawal letter to the committee. Read also:  PDP crises: Abaribe withdraws from Abia guber primary Ogidi said that no reason was given for their withdrawal but they have assured the party of their continued support and loyalty. “Out of the six contestants that bought forms for the election, four of them have willingly withdrawn from the race. They have given us their letters and the reasons for their withdrawal. The beauty of it is that they have not left the party,” he said.